✅ 7x faster than HDDs and 3x faster than traditional SSDs.
✅ Up to 4TB storage.
✅ 6 optimized ports.
✅ Comparable with any device that has Type-C.

They are now live on Indiegogo and you still have time to get it with 54% OFF. Check the link in our bio or visit @jointurbohub

node.text: An #el­ectric motor is all about #magnets and magnetism: A #motor uses magnets to create motion. If you have ever played with magnets you know about the fundamental law of all magnets: Opposites attract and likes repel. So if you have two bar magnets with their ends marked "north" and "south," then the north end of one magnet will attract the south end of the other. On the other hand, the north end of one magnet will repel the north end of the other (and similarly, south will repel south). Inside an electric motor, these attracting and repelling forces create rotational motion. ­

Follow👉 @engineeringaggle
Tea-Light Floating Engine: a candle powered super simple steam engine. The engine is just a coil of copper tubing, filled with water. The ends of the tube are bent and directed to produce counter-clockwise rotation. Steam builds up pushing water out with an explosive jet- which then results in a partial vacuum in the coil which pulls more water in to repeat the process. The water expulsion is in the form of jet directed out the end of the tube whereas the refill comes back in to the tube from a larger range of angles- so on balance the engine moves opposite to the direction of the jets.
Video by @physicsfun🌺
.
